methods.asIndex:
Get an Index representation of this OrderedKeys.

:return: (io.deephaven.db.v2.utils.Index) An Index representation for the same keys in the same order
methods.asKeyIndicesChunk:
Get a LongChunk representation of the individual keys in this OrderedKeys.

:return: (io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.LongChunk<io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.Attributes.OrderedKeyIndices>) A LongChunk containing the keys in this OrderedKeys

methods.close:
Free any resources associated with this object.
 Using any OrderedKeys methods after close() is an error and may produce exceptions or
 undefined results.
methods.fillKeyIndicesChunk:
Fill the supplied WritableLongChunk with individual keys from this OrderedKeys.
 The chunk's capacity is assumed to be big enough.

:param chunkToFill: io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.WritableLongChunk<? extends io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.Attributes.KeyIndices>
methods.fillKeyRangesChunk:
Fill the supplied WritableLongChunk with key ranges from this OrderedKeys.
 The chunk's capacity is assumed to be big enough.

:param chunkToFill: io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.WritableLongChunk<io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.Attributes.OrderedKeyRanges>
methods.firstKey:
Get the first key in this OrderedKeys.

:return: (long) The first key, or ReadOnlyIndex.NULL_KEY if there is none.
methods.forEachLong:
For as long as the consumer wants more keys, call accept on the consumer with the individual key instances
 in this OrderedKeys, in increasing order.

:param lc: io.deephaven.db.v2.utils.LongAbortableConsumer
:return: (boolean) false if the consumer provided ever returned false, true otherwise.
methods.forEachLongRange:
For as long as the consumer wants more ranges, call accept on the consumer with the individual key ranges
 in this OrderedKeys, in increasing order.

:param lrac: io.deephaven.db.v2.utils.LongRangeAbortableConsumer
:return: (boolean) false if the consumer provided ever returned false, true otherwise.
methods.getAverageRunLengthEstimate:
Get an estimate of the average (mean) length of runs of adjacent keys in this OrderedKeys.
 Implementations should strive to keep this method efficient (O(1) preferred) at the expense of
 accuracy.
 Empty OrderedKeys should return an arbitrary valid value, usually 1.

:return: (long) An estimate of the average run length in this OrderedKeys, in [1, size()]
methods.getOrderedKeysByKeyRange:
Get an ordered subset of the keys in this OrderedKeys for a key range. The returned set will be the
 intersection of the keys in this  with the keys in the closed interval
 [startKeyInclusive, endKeyInclusive].

 The returned reference is owned by the caller, who should call close() when it is done with it.

:param startKeyInclusive: long
:param endKeyInclusive: long
:return: (io.deephaven.db.v2.utils.OrderedKeys) The subset as an OrderedKeys, which may be this
methods.getOrderedKeysByPosition:
Get an ordered subset of the keys in this OrderedKeys for a position range.
 The result will contain the set of keys in this that lie at positions in the half-open range
 [startPositionInclusive, startPositionInclusive + length).

 The returned reference is owned by the caller, who should call close() when it is done with it.

:param startPositionInclusive: long
:param length: long
:return: (io.deephaven.db.v2.utils.OrderedKeys) The subset as an OrderedKeys, which may be this
methods.getOrderedKeysIterator:

:return: (io.deephaven.db.v2.utils.OrderedKeys.Iterator) A new iterator, positioned at the first key
methods.isEmpty:
True if the size of this Orderedkeys is zero.

:return: (boolean) True if there are no elements in this OrderedKeys.
methods.lastKey:
Get the last key in this OrderedKeys.

:return: (long) The last key, or ReadOnlyIndex.NULL_KEY if there is none.
methods.size:
